Cookie and nut sales are made to the public through door to door sales, and other one on one asks. Cookies sales are not made through retail venues.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Part V, Line 4: Intended uses of the endowment fund.
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Earnings on the endowment fund are used to provide scholarships to girls in the areas of Agriculture and STEM. They are recorded as temporarily restricted income in the year they are received.

The Council is exempt from federal income taxes under Section 501(c)(3) of the Internal Revenue Code as a charitable organization whereby only unrelated business income, as defined by Section 509(a)(1) of the Code, is subject to federal income tax. Accordingly, no provision for current or deferred income taxes has been recorded. The Council uses the same accounting methods for tax and financial reporting purposes.GAAP provides accounting and disclosure guidance about positions taken by an entity in its tax returns that might be uncertain. Management has considered its tax positions and believes that all of the positions taken in its federal and state exempt organiztion tax returns are more likely than not to be sustained upon examination.The income tax returns for the three prior year for federal and four prior years for state income tax purposes are subject to examiniation by appropriate tax authorities. Interest and penalties, if imposed from tax positions, are recognized in the financial statements as operating expenses.

THE COUNCIL PROVIDES FUNDING FOR GIRLS AND ADULTS TO PAY DUES, AND ATTEND CAMPING AND OTHER ENRICHMENT PROGRAMS. THE FUNDS ARE AVAILABLE FOR USE BY MEMBERS MEETING SPECIFIC REQUIREMENTS. THE FUNDS ARE CREDITED TO THE ATTENDEES ACCOUNT AND ARE NOT ISSUED TO THE INDIVIDUAL.
